{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":297718,"duration_api_ms":279545,"num_turns":31,"result":"All 4 CR18 amendments implemented and verified. Here is the ExecutionPayload:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"schema\": \"ralph-burning/execution-payload/v1\",\n  \"project_id\": \"gn8\",\n  \"stage\": \"plan_and_implement\",\n  \"cycle\": 1,\n  \"completion_round\": 18,\n  \"status\": \"completed\",\n  \"amendments_addressed\": [\n    {\n      \"id\": 1,\n      \"title\": \"CycleAdvanced should retain stale entries\",\n      \"resolution\": \"Added `retryable_failed_attempts.retain(|&(_, c), _| c >= current_cycle)` in the CycleAdvanced handler of derive_resume_state, after updating current_cycle. Drops retry history for cycles behind the cursor to avoid unbounded memory growth.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 2,\n      \"title\": \"apply_jitter uses poor randomness source\",\n      \"resolution\": \"Replaced raw `nanos % 1000` with a murmur-style hash-mixing step (`h ^= h >> 16; h = h.wrapping_mul(0x45d9f3b); h ^= h >> 16`) before the modulo. This spreads entropy across all bits so coarse-clock platforms (e.g. 1ms resolution) produce well-distributed jitter. No new dependency needed.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 3,\n      \"title\": \"CRITICAL: Clear retryable_failed_attempts on will_retry=false\",\n      \"resolution\": \"Added an `else` branch in the StageFailed handler of derive_resume_state: when `will_retry=false`, the entry is removed via `retryable_failed_attempts.remove(&(stage_id, cycle))`. This ensures a resumed run after terminal failure starts at attempt 1, fixing SC-RESUME-005 conformance. Added unit test `terminal_failure_clears_retry_tracking` verifying 4 retryable failures followed by a terminal will_retry=false results in resume attempt=1.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 4,\n      \"title\": \"Pre-backoff snapshot write should NOT be best-effort\",\n      \"resolution\": \"Reverted the `if let Err` best-effort pattern back to `?` propagation. The stage_failed journal event is already durably appended before the snapshot write; if the snapshot fails and the process crashes during backoff, journal says 'failed/retrying' but run.json is stale, producing an unresumable journal/snapshot divergence. The snapshot write must propagate errors to maintain consistency.\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"files_modified\": [\n    \"src/contexts/workflow_composition/engine.rs\",\n    \"src/contexts/workflow_composition/retry_policy.rs\"\n  ],\n  \"tests_added\": [\n    \"resume_state_tests::terminal_failure_clears_retry_tracking\"\n  ],\n  \"verification\": {\n    \"lib_tests\": \"341 passed\",\n    \"integration_tests\": \"683 passed\",\n    \"clippy\": \"clean\",\n    \"fmt\": \"clean\"\n  }\n}\n```","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"2ab56341-dc03-426c-ace5-dda05f3b0827","total_cost_usd":2.2091632499999996,"usage":{"input_tokens":28,"cache_creation_input_tokens":41054,"cache_read_input_tokens":1038096,"output_tokens":8175,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":41054,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"},"modelUsage":{"claude-opus-4-6":{"inputTokens":32394,"outputTokens":14192,"cacheReadInputTokens":1049399,"cacheCreationInputTokens":186831,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":2.2091632499999996,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":64000}},"permission_denials":[],"fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"8a36af12-df19-4616-817a-309966bd9146"}
